response: #5, #7, #12, #17, #23  As a university student, I advocate for improved mobility within the city that supports an eco-friendly lifestyle, hence my preference for bike lanes and safe biking environments reveals an inclination to prioritize both safety and sustainable transportation. Promoting a car-less vision like the Lastrasse to increase pedestrian space reflects similar sustainability values. Facilitating cost-free access to spaces (such as open water) where I and other students can unwind enhances our quality of life in what is often a busy and structured academic schedule. Lastly, supporting resources for easy and shared transport connects with financial consciousness and team spirit, a characteristic typical for vibrant student communities.

response: #5, #6, #11, #17, #23  As a university student living in Zurich and being invested in environmental and sustainable causes as a foundation to my choices, here's a short explanation of why I chose these projects: - Safe Bike Paths around Irchel Park: Makes commuting to the university safer. - More Night Buses to Oerlikon: Improves accessibility and enhances late-night safe transport. - Free Bike Fixing Workshops: As a bike commuter, acquiring these skills can help me massively as well as others who rely on cycling. - Bike Lanes on Seefeldstrasse: Facilitates my bicycle travel to the Zurich Lake for leisure and encourages healthy lifestyles. - Public Bicycle Moving Trailer to be Borrowed: Promotes sustainable relocation methods for students moving residence often.
